It is!<p>But sometimes you end up using it to make code more reliable, as in:<p><pre><code>    do_thing($_) for @things;
</code></pre>
Where $_ is passed in as an argument, as opposed to:<p><pre><code>    do_thing for @things;
</code></pre>
Where $_ is (due to its global nature) set by `for`, and read in sub do_thing { ... }
